</P></DIV><A id=3Dcomment-1159898330000 =
name=3Dcomment-1159898330000></A>
<DIV class=3D"comment odd" id=3Dcomment5>Hi Michael, I'm glad to see =
that you and=20
the Hamburg team have a blog now. As I saw in Lyon, the team has a lot =
of energy=20
and great ideas, and it is good to have an additional avenue for sharing =
that.=20
<P>I just got back from the KDE aKademy 2006 conference in Dublin. =
KOffice also=20
has the starts of a toolkit, using their Kross scripting framework with =
a Python=20
wrapper. So it appears to be an idea whose time has come.=20
<P>To your three questions:=20
<P>Bindings: Java, C++ and Python would be my preference.=20
<P>Scope: I think we need creation, reading, writing and modifying.=20
<P>Abstraction: I'd start simple and evolve from there. No one wants to =
create a=20
complicated styled document from an API. Better to create the =
complicated=20
document in OpenOffice and leave a few placeholders for data to be =
written (a=20
template) and then have a simple API that will fill in the missing data. =
This=20
gives a nice separation of roles -- the business person creates the =
document=20
that looks the way he wants it to look and the app developer hooks it up =
to the=20
data sources.=20
